				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Do Bards No Longer Get Intimidate at 26?<a name="54981"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 3 04 5:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I used it when I fear-snared Nezzie and Eldrig for my epic. (I was low enough level that I wanted every possible advantage I could get.)  Put it on the song key for your fear song.  Why?  Two reasons:
<br />

<br />
1)  Fear song can be resisted, Intimidation is a backup.
<br />
2)  The range of Fear song is tiny.  
<br />

<br />
When you are doing a mob like Nezzie (a named wurm) you gotta be in JUST the right spot, 2.5 degrees to the right of the mob's buttcrack just to be hitting the d*mn thing, let alone land your fear song.  Intimidation seems to have a slightly better range, or something, cause even more than on other mobs, Nezzie got feared by Intimidation rather than my song.
<br />

<br />
But then, in these days of twinks etc. and the way people often brag, most folks will just tell you how easy Nezzie was for them.  That beeotch has killed me LOTS of times now (I have helped a lot of other bards with the camp, of course).  The most important thing you can do is KEEP HER FEARED so she can't nuke you or gate.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
